I'm gonna go.

253
00:20:52,099 --> 00:20:54,668
Ten minutes.
I promise.

254
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,215
[Sighs]

255
00:21:10,652 --> 00:21:13,520
I don't know, Richard.

256
00:21:13,588 --> 00:21:15,922
Maybe they don't
like police in this town.

257
00:21:17,825 --> 00:21:20,093
What? You think I'm
doing this on purpose?

258
00:21:20,961 --> 00:21:23,096
[Honking]

259
00:21:31,639 --> 00:21:33,173
I think you need
a new phone.

260
00:21:34,909 --> 00:21:36,410
Yeah.

261
00:21:37,378 --> 00:21:40,046
It's pretty bad.
The lugs are rusted.

262
00:21:40,114 --> 00:21:43,783
I think I'm just gonna
call a tow truck.

263
00:21:43,851 --> 00:21:45,885
Let me give it a try.

264
00:21:45,953 --> 00:21:47,554
All right.
Knock yourself out.

265
00:22:02,370 --> 00:22:04,738
Well, you're stronger
then you look.

266
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,642
Is that supposed
to be a compliment?

267
00:22:08,710 --> 00:22:10,477
No. I'm sorry.

268
00:22:10,545 --> 00:22:14,914
I'm just not being used to being
the damsel in distress type.

269
00:22:14,982 --> 00:22:18,252
- I'm Teresa by the way.
- I know who you are.

270
00:22:18,319 --> 00:22:21,054
- Really?
- Yeah.

271
00:22:21,122 --> 00:22:22,956
I've seen you on TV.

272
00:22:23,023 --> 00:22:26,926
I know.
Larry Childs has made me famous unfortunately.

273
00:22:26,994 --> 00:22:28,862
I heard, uh,

274
00:22:28,929 --> 00:22:31,931
he's trying to...
make a deal or something?

275
00:22:31,999 --> 00:22:33,634
Think he'll get off?

276
00:22:33,701 --> 00:22:36,002
I don't know.

277
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:38,272
It's out of my hands really.

278
00:22:42,543 --> 00:22:45,646
You need any help down there?
No, I got it.

279
00:22:45,713 --> 00:22:47,213
All right.

280
00:22:53,721 --> 00:22:56,055
You're all set.

281
00:22:56,123 --> 00:22:58,858
Well, thank you again.

282
00:23:00,261 --> 00:23:03,096
- Hey, I still didn't get your name.
- Sean.

283
00:23:03,164 --> 00:23:05,465
Can I offer you a ride
now that you fixed my tire?

284
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:08,435
Oh, no. No, thanks.
I take the train.

285
00:23:08,503 --> 00:23:10,337
You sure?
Yeah.

286
00:23:11,372 --> 00:23:12,639
Good night.

287
00:23:56,818 --> 00:23:59,853
[Blows Landing
On Punching Bag]

288
00:24:21,642 --> 00:24:24,043
Sean. Sean.
Hey, Sean.

289
00:24:24,111 --> 00:24:26,546
Whoa! Hey!

290
00:24:26,614 --> 00:24:28,114
[Laughing]

291
00:24:28,182 --> 00:24:29,516
Yeah.
Sorry about that, Dad.

292
00:24:29,584 --> 00:24:32,352
That's okay.
Oh.

293
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:36,556
I thought I was gonna end up with a matching shiner.
Let me look at that.

294
00:24:39,126 --> 00:24:42,262
Yeah, you're still not upset
about the fight, are ya?

295
00:24:42,329 --> 00:24:43,463
Hmm?

296
00:24:45,399 --> 00:24:48,802
It's nothing to be ashamed of.
Nothing to be ashamed of.

297
00:24:50,772 --> 00:24:54,975
I had my head handed to me
more than a couple times.

298
00:24:55,043 --> 00:24:57,243
Can you get that for me?

299
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:00,380
All right.

300
00:25:00,448 --> 00:25:04,284
I'm standing here.
Damn, you look good. Nice and smooth.

301
00:25:04,351 --> 00:25:06,620
Fluid. Chin down.

302
00:25:08,355 --> 00:25:11,357
You could be getting more power
behind your straight right.

303
00:25:11,425 --> 00:25:14,861
You wanna pivot.
Pivot on the back foot.

304
00:25:14,929 --> 00:25:17,497
Throw your shoulder into it
with just a little bit more.

305
00:25:17,565 --> 00:25:19,165
Tuck your chin down
a little bit.

306
00:25:19,233 --> 00:25:21,001
You know, just-- just--

307
00:25:21,069 --> 00:25:22,569
You know, just--

308
00:25:24,371 --> 00:25:29,309
Be nice and fluid on the jab.
Pivot. Put your shoulder into it.

309
00:25:29,376 --> 00:25:33,313
That's it. These street fighter motherfuckers,
they don't give a shit about technique.

310
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:36,516
So don't be afraid to get
the most of it, Sean.

311
00:25:45,727 --> 00:25:47,761
Well, you get the idea.

312
00:25:47,829 --> 00:25:50,196
Yeah, I get the idea.

313
00:25:55,069 --> 00:25:57,403
Your birthday's coming up.

314
00:26:00,074 --> 00:26:02,776
Yeah, I know.

315
00:26:02,844 --> 00:26:04,845
I'm thinking maybe
we could do something.

316
00:26:10,184 --> 00:26:12,185
I'll call you
when supper is ready.

317
00:26:25,066 --> 00:26:26,633
Fuck you.

318
00:26:30,271 --> 00:26:33,306
He is a little boy!
You drunk son of a bitch!

319
00:26:33,374 --> 00:26:36,509
Lower your voice.
Lower your-- I will fucking kill you!

320
00:26:36,577 --> 00:26:40,480
- Do you understand? - I wanted him go to his room!
That's exactly what I mean!

321
00:26:40,548 --> 00:26:44,484
Believe it or not, he's gonna fucking listen
to me when I tell him to do something!

322
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:47,921
Say that one more fucking time.
You touch him again...

323
00:26:47,989 --> 00:26:49,489
and I will fucking kill you!

324
00:26:49,557 --> 00:26:51,958
Giving me orders now?
Is that what you're fucking doing?

325
00:26:52,026 --> 00:26:56,362
[Shouting, Indistinct]

326
00:27:02,070 --> 00:27:04,171
Who the fuck do you think
you are talking to?

327
00:27:05,639 --> 00:27:08,675
My fucking house,
and I don't like the way you fucking said it!

328
00:27:08,743 --> 00:27:11,211
Just shut your fucking mouth!

329
00:27:27,195 --> 00:27:28,729
So what do you think?

330
00:27:28,796 --> 00:27:31,564
About what?

331
00:27:31,632 --> 00:27:33,700
About his story.

332
00:27:33,768 --> 00:27:36,703
I think a drug dealer got
popped and he's dead.

333
00:27:36,771 --> 00:27:38,271
That's what I think.

334
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:40,306
[Sighs]
Want anything?

335
00:27:40,374 --> 00:27:42,242
No, I'm good.

336
00:27:42,309 --> 00:27:46,980
I also think that more than likely
that little criminal in there killed him.

337
00:27:47,048 --> 00:27:50,683
But of course we're never going
to know that because as usual...

338
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:54,687
nobody saw nothin'
and we got no murder weapon.

339
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:58,158
So you don't believe anything
he said about that other guy?

340
00:27:58,226 --> 00:28:00,026
No.

341
00:28:00,094 --> 00:28:02,763
What I know...

342
00:28:02,830 --> 00:28:05,565
is that a patrol car saw
our boy and the victim...

343
00:28:05,633 --> 00:28:08,434
working their usual spot
the night of the murder.

344
00:28:08,502 --> 00:28:10,336
Couple of hours later,
Tony's dead.

345
00:28:10,404 --> 00:28:11,905
And the next night...

346
00:28:11,973 --> 00:28:14,274
junior mafia in there
takes over the business.

347
00:28:14,341 --> 00:28:15,976
My money's on him.

348
00:28:16,043 --> 00:28:18,444
Tony was a pretty
serious guy.

349
00:28:18,512 --> 00:28:20,613
It's a little ambitious for
that kid. He's too young.

350
00:28:24,118 --> 00:28:25,752
Did you grow up in
a big family, Ames?

351
00:28:25,820 --> 00:28:29,489
Yeah, I did.
Why?

352
00:28:29,556 --> 00:28:31,624
- That explains it.
- Explains what?

353
00:28:33,627 --> 00:28:35,762
You've got
"look at me" syndrome.

354
00:28:36,998 --> 00:28:39,732
- What?
- Oh, yeah.

355
00:28:39,801 --> 00:28:42,368
Yeah, you come from
a big family, see,

356
00:28:42,436 --> 00:28:44,171
so it's hard for you
to get attention.

357
00:28:44,238 --> 00:28:46,273
It's hard for Mommy and Daddy
to notice you.

358
00:28:46,340 --> 00:28:47,440
Really?
Yeah.

359
00:28:47,508 --> 00:28:49,642
So you gotta make a big deal
out of everything.

360
00:28:49,710 --> 00:28:52,946
Oh, boy.
No, I mean you gotta over achieve.

361
00:28:53,014 --> 00:28:55,315
You have to excel
at all costs.

362
00:28:55,382 --> 00:28:58,051
"Look at me" syndrome.
I see.

363
00:28:59,586 --> 00:29:03,423
And you've deduced this from what?
Me wanting to do my job?

364
00:29:03,490 --> 00:29:06,559
Or should I say,
wanting to do our job.

365
00:29:06,627 --> 00:29:08,829
All I'm saying is...

366
00:29:08,896 --> 00:29:12,966
don't make more out of this
than it actually is.

367
00:29:13,034 --> 00:29:16,369
Look, there are a hundred people
out there that wanted Tony dead.

368
00:29:16,437 --> 00:29:18,338
He was a true piece of shit,

369
00:29:18,405 --> 00:29:21,007
drug-dealing pedophile,
I might add.

370
00:29:21,075 --> 00:29:24,077
But in the end...

371
00:29:24,145 --> 00:29:27,214
killer is usually the first guy
that comes to mind.

372
00:29:27,281 --> 00:29:29,216
Really?
Yeah.

373
00:29:29,283 --> 00:29:33,320
Thank you. It's great.
Homicide 101. I can manage.

374
00:29:34,588 --> 00:29:36,456
- I'm just trying to help.
- You wanna help me?

375
00:29:36,523 --> 00:29:39,759
- Yeah.
- Go get me some coffee. That's how you can help me.

376
00:29:41,262 --> 00:29:43,063
Only if you come with me.

377
00:29:46,968 --> 00:29:49,269
Here.

378
00:29:55,609 --> 00:29:58,111
What's his story?

379
00:29:58,179 --> 00:30:01,181
Who, Sean?
Man.

380
00:30:01,249 --> 00:30:04,184
Mother got her head blown off
right in front of his face.

381
00:30:04,252 --> 00:30:06,286
Like 10 years ago.

382
00:30:06,354 --> 00:30:08,321
Car jacking.

383
00:30:08,389 --> 00:30:10,723
That's horrible.
Yeah.

384
00:30:10,791 --> 00:30:14,227
He's been coming in here
ever since then.

385
00:30:14,295 --> 00:30:15,996
Baldwin lets him look
at mug shots,

386
00:30:16,063 --> 00:30:18,365
see if the guy got grabbed
for something else.

387
00:30:18,432 --> 00:30:21,001
So he just let's him come in and
use the computer unattended?

388
00:30:21,068 --> 00:30:23,836
That's not exactly
procedure, is it?

389
00:30:23,905 --> 00:30:27,673
Bill's senior man on the squad, Ames.
I don't ask questions.

390
00:30:34,481 --> 00:30:37,450
And he's a little young for you,
don't you think, Detective?

391
00:30:37,518 --> 00:30:39,719
[Laughing]
You're a jerk.

392
00:30:39,787 --> 00:30:43,056
No, he helped me change a tire on my car the other day.

393
00:30:43,124 --> 00:30:45,325
I just think he's
a nice kid, that's all.

394
00:30:45,393 --> 00:30:47,460
That's sweet.

395
00:30:47,528 --> 00:30:49,062
Look. You, uh--

396
00:30:49,130 --> 00:30:51,597
You ready to go?
Junior mafia is about to call his lawyer.

397
00:30:51,665 --> 00:30:54,801
Yeah, I'll meet you
in there in a minute.

398
00:30:54,868 --> 00:30:56,602
[Laughing]

399
00:31:08,549 --> 00:31:10,583
He's an ugly one.

400
00:31:12,353 --> 00:31:15,355
I find them all
to be pretty ugly.

401
00:31:15,423 --> 00:31:17,890
I wanted to say thank you for the other night.
For helping me.

402
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:20,526
Oh. It's-- It's not a problem.

403
00:31:20,594 --> 00:31:24,364
So now I owe you one.
I was thinking maybe I could help you with your work.

404
00:31:24,432 --> 00:31:26,032
I'm pretty good
at what I do.

405
00:31:26,100 --> 00:31:28,034
Okay.
Ames!

406
00:31:28,102 --> 00:31:31,137
Let's go.
I'll be right there.

407
00:31:32,506 --> 00:31:33,873
So it's a deal?

408
00:31:33,941 --> 00:31:36,576
I'll take a look at your case,
see how I can give you a hand,

409
00:31:36,643 --> 00:31:40,680
and we'll talk about it.
You really don't have to do that.

410
00:31:40,747 --> 00:31:42,548
You don't want my help?

411
00:31:42,616 --> 00:31:44,617
No, no.
Then don't worry about it.

412
00:31:44,685 --> 00:31:47,854
I'll take a look at it, okay?
I gotta go.

413
00:32:13,147 --> 00:32:15,248
I need a girl.

414
00:32:17,818 --> 00:32:20,887
[Crying]

415
00:32:24,658 --> 00:32:26,859
[Man] Did you take that vitamin C I gave you?

416
00:32:28,029 --> 00:32:29,929
Yes, I did. Thank you.

417
00:32:31,499 --> 00:32:34,000
I want you to wear your
heavy coat tonight, okay?

418
00:32:34,068 --> 00:32:37,603
I don't want this to get
any worse then it is.

419
00:32:37,671 --> 00:32:39,672
[Woman]
Joe.

420
00:32:42,743 --> 00:32:44,610
I don't think--

421
00:32:47,381 --> 00:32:49,582
You don't think what?

422
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:53,353
- I'm sick, Joe.
- Yeah, I know.

423
00:32:53,421 --> 00:32:56,589
That's why I'm trying to do everything
I can to make you feel better.

424
00:32:59,193 --> 00:33:01,094
I don't want to do this, okay?

425
00:33:02,096 --> 00:33:05,532
I'm sorry,
but I can't do this tonight.

426
00:33:07,268 --> 00:33:11,137
I fucking told you to get up!
Get up! [Screaming]

427
00:33:11,205 --> 00:33:13,540
I waited and waited for you!

428
00:33:13,607 --> 00:33:16,309
I worry about you
all fucking day!

429
00:33:16,377 --> 00:33:19,479
And all you can do
is think about yourself!

430
00:33:19,547 --> 00:33:21,814
You selfish fucking bitch!

431
00:33:21,882 --> 00:33:23,683
Now you are gonna
go that job,

432
00:33:23,750 --> 00:33:25,351
and you are
gonna like it!

433
00:33:25,419 --> 00:33:29,155
Get in the fucking car!
Get in the car!

434
00:33:33,127 --> 00:33:35,128
Leave her--
Leave her alone.

435
00:33:35,196 --> 00:33:37,930
Motherfucker!

436
00:33:43,437 --> 00:33:44,937
Joe, don't!

437
00:33:45,005 --> 00:33:46,973
[Woman Screaming]

438
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:50,343
You mind your own
fucking business!

439
00:33:52,213 --> 00:33:54,780
- You picked the wrong fucking guy!
- Stop! Please!

440
00:33:56,917 --> 00:33:58,918
- Sticking your nose into my business.
- [Screaming]

441
00:33:58,986 --> 00:34:00,320
Shut up!

442
00:34:06,059 --> 00:34:09,329
Fucker!

443
00:34:09,396 --> 00:34:10,597
Ow. Ow!

444
00:34:13,667 --> 00:34:15,468
[Woman]
Joe, please don't!

445
00:34:32,419 --> 00:34:33,620
[Crying]

446
00:34:38,292 --> 00:34:40,260
Get in the house!

447
00:34:40,327 --> 00:34:43,062
Get inside! This is
all your fault!

448
00:34:50,171 --> 00:34:52,104
Who the fuck
do you think you are?

449
00:34:52,173 --> 00:34:55,575
You come around here again,
and I will put a bullet in your head.

450
00:34:55,643 --> 00:34:57,710
And that bitch you
tried to save--

451
00:34:57,778 --> 00:35:01,747
I am going to beat her
until she can't fucking move.

452
00:35:03,016 --> 00:35:07,053
So you haven't done anything
here except waste my time.

453
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,888
Fuck up my car.

454
00:35:10,291 --> 00:35:12,625
You didn't save her.

455
00:35:12,693 --> 00:35:14,260
You made it worse.

456
00:35:15,762 --> 00:35:17,430
Hey, Joe.

457
00:35:20,901 --> 00:35:24,837
[Woman Screaming]

458
00:36:26,467 --> 00:36:28,268
[Teresa] Did you ever see this man before?

459
00:36:28,335 --> 00:36:30,503
I meet a lot of men.

460
00:36:30,571 --> 00:36:33,139
It's hard to keep track.
Thanks, sweetie.

461
00:36:38,345 --> 00:36:40,480
You know what I do, right?

462
00:36:40,547 --> 00:36:42,114
Yeah, you're a hooker.
Gary.

463
00:36:43,651 --> 00:36:45,785
Miss Winston,
I know what you do.

464
00:36:45,852 --> 00:36:48,588
Please, call me Lizzy.

465
00:36:48,656 --> 00:36:52,492
Miss Winston is my mother,
and I don't want to think about her right now.

466
00:36:52,559 --> 00:36:54,460
So you're telling me
you didn't recognize him?

467
00:36:54,528 --> 00:36:57,697
I never saw this guy before.

468
00:36:57,765 --> 00:36:59,666
Anyways, I couldn't really
tell what he looked like.

469
00:36:59,733 --> 00:37:04,370
He had this black outfit on,
and it was kind of dark out.

470
00:37:04,438 --> 00:37:07,006
Do you know anybody who didn't particularly like Joey?

471
00:37:07,073 --> 00:37:10,343
Maybe someone
who wanted him dead?

472
00:37:10,411 --> 00:37:14,213
- Who didn't want him dead?
- Lizzy I'm going to have a sketch artist come up here.

473
00:37:14,281 --> 00:37:17,183
Look, Miss Detective,

474
00:37:17,250 --> 00:37:20,219
Joe was a piece of shit.

475
00:37:20,287 --> 00:37:22,322
He was going to kill me.

476
00:37:23,424 --> 00:37:26,158
Maybe not last night, but...

477
00:37:26,226 --> 00:37:30,563
sooner or later he was going to
hit me too hard or choke me.

478
00:37:30,631 --> 00:37:33,065
That little girl he killed--

479
00:37:33,133 --> 00:37:34,934
Now what are
you talking about?

480
00:37:35,001 --> 00:37:37,870
Mancini was charged with murdering a 13-year-old girl.

481
00:37:37,938 --> 00:37:40,373
- He beat the charge.
- Yeah.

482
00:37:40,441 --> 00:37:42,942
He used to laugh about that.

483
00:37:43,009 --> 00:37:46,579
He was gonna kill me next.

484
00:37:46,647 --> 00:37:49,415
That guy...

485
00:37:49,483 --> 00:37:51,551
saved my life.

486
00:37:53,019 --> 00:37:54,587
He was...

487
00:37:54,655 --> 00:37:56,856
sent down by God
to save me.

488
00:37:56,923 --> 00:38:01,694
You know,
I'm getting a second chance now 'cause of him and--

489
00:38:01,762 --> 00:38:06,265
You know, you seem like
a real nice person, but...

490
00:38:06,333 --> 00:38:08,701
I'm not going to help you
arrest this guy.

491
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:13,840
Just wouldn't be fair.

492
00:38:13,907 --> 00:38:15,975
[Phone Ringing]

493
00:38:17,944 --> 00:38:20,112
Teresa Ames.

494
00:38:20,180 --> 00:38:21,581
Yeah.

495
00:38:23,917 --> 00:38:26,753
The 21-- no problem.
Okay.

496
00:38:28,589 --> 00:38:30,590
Shit.
What's up?

497
00:38:30,657 --> 00:38:33,993
The fucking Delany case
has been delayed again.

498
00:38:34,060 --> 00:38:36,729
Larry Childs is trying to
cut a deal with the D.A.

499
00:38:36,797 --> 00:38:39,331
[Sighs]
I can't believe this shit.

500
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,801
So, what do you care?

501
00:38:41,869 --> 00:38:44,537
Fuck 'em. We get paid
to catch 'em. After that...

