you know that?

600
00:45:02,682 --> 00:45:04,984
I know. It's my job.
I can't help myself.

601
00:45:05,051 --> 00:45:08,353
But you're right, so go ahead.
Ask me a question.

602
00:45:08,421 --> 00:45:10,789
How long were you
married for?

603
00:45:10,857 --> 00:45:13,258
How do you know
I was married?

604
00:45:13,326 --> 00:45:16,695
I-I read an article in the paper.
It said you were married.

605
00:45:16,763 --> 00:45:20,099
Okay, so how do you know
I'm divorced?

606
00:45:20,166 --> 00:45:22,267
Well, for starters,
you're not wearing a ring.

607
00:45:23,269 --> 00:45:25,470
What if it gets
in the way of my work?

608
00:45:25,538 --> 00:45:28,473
Nah, you're not married
anymore. I can tell.

609
00:45:28,541 --> 00:45:31,076
And how can you tell,
Detective Donovan? Tell me.

610
00:45:33,179 --> 00:45:36,148
There's a sadness
in your eyes.

611
00:45:36,215 --> 00:45:38,017
