it's not for my ex-husband.

613
00:45:41,621 --> 00:45:43,122
Believe me.

614
00:45:44,824 --> 00:45:47,459
It would be more for my son.

615
00:45:47,527 --> 00:45:51,030
Yeah.
Richard-- he had, um--

616
00:45:51,097 --> 00:45:53,598
He had better lawyers and...

617
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:55,267
a lot more money.

618
00:45:55,334 --> 00:45:59,638
I was working all the time,
so I guess in the end it really was my fault.

619
00:45:59,706 --> 00:46:04,209
I have... weekends and
every other Wednesday.

620
00:46:05,545 --> 00:46:07,913
What's your son's name?
Tyler.

621
00:46:07,981 --> 00:46:09,682
Tyler.

622
00:46:09,749 --> 00:46:12,250
