there's no way around that.

673
00:49:26,513 --> 00:49:28,680
Due process.

674
00:49:34,287 --> 00:49:36,121
This was my mother,
Detective.

675
00:49:38,091 --> 00:49:39,958
She taught little kids music.

676
00:49:41,594 --> 00:49:44,629
It's not like she died
in a car accident...

677
00:49:44,697 --> 00:49:47,099
or died of cancer.

678
00:49:48,301 --> 00:49:51,370
She was murdered.

679
00:49:51,438 --> 00:49:53,405
Murdered trying
to protect me.

680
00:49:56,376 --> 00:49:59,878
Somebody...
made the decision...

681
00:49:59,946 --> 00:50:02,281
to end her life.

682
00:50:03,483 --> 00:50:06,985
The piece of shit
walks around every day.

683
00:50:07,053 --> 00:50:09,020
Going through it...

684
00:50:09,089 --> 00:50:10,589
like it never happened.

685
00:50:14,394 --> 00:50:16,361
Due process.

686
00:50:19,165 --> 00:50:22,968
How'd due process work out for
you in the Child's case Teresa?

687
00:50:24,637 --> 00:50:27,272
Scumbag kills two fucking people
and now they're talking about...

688
00:50:27,340 --> 00:50:30,342
