from the other night.

986
01:10:06,918 --> 01:10:09,753
I was a little drunk that night.
I might have been a little out of line.

987
01:10:09,821 --> 01:10:11,188
No. You were
a lot out of line.

988
01:10:11,256 --> 01:10:13,390
Well, you're out of line coming to my house uninvited.

989
01:10:13,458 --> 01:10:15,125
I need some answers
about Sean.

990
01:10:15,193 --> 01:10:17,661
Leave him alone.
That's your answer.

991
01:10:17,728 --> 01:10:20,130
I can't do that anymore.

992
01:10:22,667 --> 01:10:24,168
Let's have a drink.

993
01:10:29,540 --> 01:10:31,375
[Baldwin Narrating]
I was 10 years on the squad...

994
01:10:31,443 --> 01:10:33,777
when they brought that kid
into the station.

995
01:10:35,513 --> 01:10:40,150
They should have brought him to the hospital.
He was in shock.

996
01:10:40,218 --> 01:10:42,019
No emotion.

997
01:10:42,087 --> 01:10:43,988
No crying.

998
01:10:44,055 --> 01:10:45,889
He'd just stare.

999
01:10:47,925 --> 01:10:51,128
Those eyes looking
right through you.

1000
01:10:51,196 --> 01:10:52,496
I wanted him to have
a look at the mugs...

1001
01:10:52,563 --> 01:10:54,865
while the perp's face
was still on his mind.

1002
01:10:54,932 --> 01:10:57,634
Him and his father.
His father saw this guy up close.

1003
01:10:57,702 --> 01:11:00,170
He pistol-whipped him
outside the car.

1004
01:11:01,339 --> 01:11:03,273
Sean was all for it.

1005
01:11:03,341 --> 01:11:05,742
Sat there for
three hours straight.

1006
01:11:07,379 --> 01:11:08,879
Sure enough...

1007
01:11:08,946 --> 01:11:10,947
picks this guy out
just like that.

1008
01:11:14,085 --> 01:11:16,286
[No Audible Dialogue]

1009
01:11:17,788 --> 01:11:20,657
But when we showed
the photo to his father,

1010
01:11:20,725 --> 01:11:22,659
he says,
"No. That's the wrong guy."

1011
01:11:24,496 --> 01:11:26,830
The kid looks at his father
like he's crazy.

1012
01:11:26,898 --> 01:11:30,567
Sean knows
this is the guy.

1013
01:11:32,870 --> 01:11:35,672
Mr. Donovan pulls Sean
to the side.

1014
01:11:35,740 --> 01:11:40,244
Gives him a lecture about the
consequences of his action.

1015
01:11:41,679 --> 01:11:44,048
The first time he'd
dealt with consequences.

1016
01:11:47,085 --> 01:11:48,618
Sean takes another look
at the photo.

1017
01:11:48,686 --> 01:11:51,905
Says he made a mistake.
His father's right. It's not the guy.

1018
01:11:57,762 --> 01:11:59,896
I felt bad for the kid.

1019
01:12:00,798 --> 01:12:02,633
He's about my son's age.

1020
01:12:04,202 --> 01:12:06,403
You know, he never
talked about his mother.

1021
01:12:06,471 --> 01:12:08,739
Never.

1022
01:12:08,806 --> 01:12:10,507
Never talked about
that night.

1023
01:12:12,510 --> 01:12:14,278
I remember
that con's name though.

1024
01:12:14,346 --> 01:12:17,348
I didn't even know it was still in my
head till about six months ago...

1025
01:12:17,415 --> 01:12:20,251
when I saw his picture
in the paper.

1026
01:12:20,318 --> 01:12:22,686
Seemed some hotshot detective...

1027
01:12:22,754 --> 01:12:26,457
arrested him for the murder
of Angela Delany.

1028
01:12:27,726 --> 01:12:29,426
Jesus Christ.

1029
01:12:30,662 --> 01:12:32,663
Larry Childs.

1030
01:12:32,731 --> 01:12:35,766
<i>Yeah.
Larry Childs.</i>

1031
01:12:38,035 --> 01:12:39,637
Do you think
he killed his mother?

1032
01:12:39,704 --> 01:12:41,204
I don't know.

1033
01:12:41,273 --> 01:12:43,474
He was a career criminal
before you busted him.

1034
01:12:43,541 --> 01:12:46,042
All I know is,
when that article came out,

1035
01:12:46,110 --> 01:12:48,111
something snapped
in that kid.

1036
01:12:48,179 --> 01:12:51,248
He was different after that.

1037
01:12:51,316 --> 01:12:53,284
He was convinced...

1038
01:12:53,351 --> 01:12:55,486
Childs killed his mother.

1039
01:12:57,054 --> 01:13:00,658
Sad thing is,
I know his father must have seen that article too.

1040
01:13:04,128 --> 01:13:09,533
Can you imagine having your son look at you every day...

1041
01:13:09,601 --> 01:13:11,468
thinking you betrayed him?

1042
01:13:13,871 --> 01:13:15,806
Can you imagine that?

1043
01:13:31,690 --> 01:13:33,123
- This yours?
- Yeah.

1044
01:13:33,191 --> 01:13:35,492
There you go.
How's it going?

1045
01:13:35,560 --> 01:13:38,028
- Is that your mom?
- Oh, yeah.

1046
01:13:38,095 --> 01:13:39,863
Yeah?

1047
01:13:39,931 --> 01:13:41,665
He's pretty cute.

1048
01:13:41,733 --> 01:13:43,300
What are you doing
here, Sean?

1049
01:13:44,736 --> 01:13:46,337
Hey, you like cake?
Yeah.

1050
01:13:46,404 --> 01:13:48,071
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1051
01:13:48,139 --> 01:13:51,375
You should really think about
taking him to Tina's in Bushwick.

1052
01:13:51,443 --> 01:13:52,976
Best cake in New York.

1053
01:13:53,044 --> 01:13:55,078
Give the ball back.
Come on. We gotta go.

1054
01:13:56,715 --> 01:13:58,349
You know, you really
shouldn't be here, Sean.

1055
01:13:58,416 --> 01:14:00,984
I wanted to talk to you
about something.

1056
01:14:01,052 --> 01:14:02,853
I-I got your address
from the station,

1057
01:14:02,920 --> 01:14:04,521
and, um, I looked it up,

1058
01:14:04,589 --> 01:14:06,890
and there was only
two parks in your area.

1059
01:14:06,958 --> 01:14:09,025
And I figured this one's
better suited for kids,

1060
01:14:09,093 --> 01:14:12,496
so I thought I'd probably
find you here.

1061
01:14:12,564 --> 01:14:14,097
Every other Wednesday, right?

1062
01:14:15,567 --> 01:14:17,868
[Horn Honking]

1063
01:14:17,935 --> 01:14:21,238
- Is that his father?
- Come on. We'll talk about it tomorrow, Sean.

1064
01:14:21,305 --> 01:14:22,873
Let's go.

1065
01:14:28,145 --> 01:14:30,614
There he is.
How was your day with your mom?

1066
01:14:30,682 --> 01:14:32,048
Good.

1067
01:14:32,116 --> 01:14:33,116
Hey.
Hey.

1068
01:14:35,353 --> 01:14:36,920
Everything okay?

1069
01:14:36,988 --> 01:14:40,123
Richard, please,
just give me one second. Please.

1070
01:14:40,191 --> 01:14:42,693
- Sean, you gotta leave right now.
- I am leaving.

1071
01:14:42,761 --> 01:14:44,728
I just wanted to thank you.

1072
01:14:44,796 --> 01:14:48,064
I'm giving it all up.
Like you said.

1073
01:14:48,132 --> 01:14:49,800
I'm moving on with my life.

1074
01:14:50,802 --> 01:14:52,403
You should move on
with yours.

1075
01:14:54,105 --> 01:14:56,407
No. This isn't over, Sean.

1076
01:14:56,474 --> 01:14:57,941
It is for me.

1077
01:15:03,080 --> 01:15:06,116
I'm sorry. I gotta go.
Bye, baby. I love you.

1078
01:15:09,387 --> 01:15:11,187
You ready?
Yeah.

1079
01:15:21,800 --> 01:15:24,601
[Chattering]

1080
01:15:26,137 --> 01:15:27,638
[Man's Voice]
Hey, Rock.

1081
01:15:46,424 --> 01:15:48,792
[Phone Vibrating]

1082
01:15:52,697 --> 01:15:55,432
<i>Hey. [Gary] Hey.
What are you doing?</i>

1083
01:15:58,703 --> 01:16:01,104
[Sighs]
I don't know.

1084
01:16:01,172 --> 01:16:02,973
Honestly.

1085
01:16:03,040 --> 01:16:06,510
Going crazy maybe.
Why? What's up?

1086
01:16:06,578 --> 01:16:09,145
<i>Uh, you see the news?</i>

1087
01:16:09,213 --> 01:16:10,781
No, why?

1088
01:16:10,849 --> 01:16:13,383
<i>Childs cut a deal.</i>

1089
01:16:13,451 --> 01:16:16,252
<i>It's official.
He must have had dirt on someone.</i>

1090
01:16:19,123 --> 01:16:21,358
What was his sentence?

1091
01:16:21,425 --> 01:16:24,027
<i>Two years.</i>

1092
01:16:24,095 --> 01:16:26,262
<i>And then he's in
the Witness Protection.</i>

1093
01:16:31,202 --> 01:16:33,370
<i>Two years.
Yeah.</i>

1094
01:16:33,437 --> 01:16:34,938
<i>Just thought
you'd want to know.</i>

1095
01:16:35,006 --> 01:16:37,207
Okay.

1096
01:16:37,274 --> 01:16:39,643
<i>Thank you.
I'm sorry, Teresa.</i>

1097
01:16:47,251 --> 01:16:48,752
Two years.

1098
01:17:05,737 --> 01:17:07,871
Mind getting me one?

1099
01:17:12,176 --> 01:17:15,612
Thanks.
I can never get my arm down far enough.

1100
01:17:16,781 --> 01:17:18,949
I'm sorry. I don't--
I don't even know your name.

1101
01:17:19,017 --> 01:17:22,218
I see you at school,
but you know how it is.

1102
01:17:22,286 --> 01:17:24,287
Sean. Sean Donovan.

1103
01:17:24,355 --> 01:17:25,923
I'm Amanda Richards.

1104
01:17:25,990 --> 01:17:28,592
How come I've never seen you
around these things before?

1105
01:17:29,594 --> 01:17:31,562
Uh, been pretty busy.

1106
01:17:32,396 --> 01:17:34,497
Hitting the books a lot.

1107
01:17:34,566 --> 01:17:36,066
Looks like
they've been hitting back.

1108
01:17:36,133 --> 01:17:38,936
That's a serious boo-boo
you got right there.

1109
01:17:39,003 --> 01:17:42,039
What happened?
Oh, um, I fell.

1110
01:17:42,874 --> 01:17:45,308
You fell?
Yeah, off my bike.

1111
01:17:45,376 --> 01:17:48,278
You fell off your bike?

1112
01:17:48,345 --> 01:17:50,047
Are you lying to me,
Sean Donovan?

1113
01:17:50,114 --> 01:17:51,448
[Chuckles]

1114
01:17:51,515 --> 01:17:54,818
Well, if you must know,

1115
01:17:54,886 --> 01:17:57,554
I, uh, got into a fight
with a pimp...

1116
01:17:57,622 --> 01:18:00,824
and he caught me in the arm
with a baseball bat.

1117
01:18:00,892 --> 01:18:03,393
It looks worse than it is.
[Laughs]

1118
01:18:03,461 --> 01:18:04,962
You're weird.

1119
01:18:07,198 --> 01:18:09,933
Hey, there's my girl.
I'm not your girl, Bruce.

1120
01:18:10,001 --> 01:18:11,935
[Bruce] You're not cheating on me,
are you?

1121
01:18:12,003 --> 01:18:14,805
- Bruce, will you take a walk?
- Hey, you go to my school.

1122
01:18:14,872 --> 01:18:17,975
- What's up, punk?
- Bruce, will you please just leave?

1123
01:18:18,042 --> 01:18:20,410
I just want to talk to
you for a second.

1124
01:18:20,478 --> 01:18:22,913
What, you can't talk
to me now?

1125
01:18:22,981 --> 01:18:26,282
- Fine. Give me a minute.
- Don't make me wait.

1126
01:18:29,386 --> 01:18:31,321
I'm sorry about that.

1127
01:18:31,388 --> 01:18:33,156
He seems like a nice guy.

1128
01:18:33,758 --> 01:18:35,291
He's not that bad.

1129
01:18:35,359 --> 01:18:37,894
Just a jerk sometimes.

1130
01:18:37,962 --> 01:18:41,431
Listen, I've got to go,
but I'll see you later, okay?

1131
01:18:41,499 --> 01:18:43,800
Don't leave.
I won't.

1132
01:18:56,447 --> 01:18:58,515
[Chattering]

1133
01:19:01,085 --> 01:19:03,987
Hey, man.
Uh, I got your--

1134
01:19:04,055 --> 01:19:05,321
This is yours.

1135
01:19:05,389 --> 01:19:07,423
What is this?

1136
01:19:15,166 --> 01:19:17,333
This isn't mine, man.
Yeah, it is.

1137
01:19:17,401 --> 01:19:20,236
No. Sorry, dude.
You got the wrong guy.

1138
01:19:20,304 --> 01:19:22,305
You could say thank you.

1139
01:19:22,373 --> 01:19:24,808
Yo, man, what are you
doing talking to freshmen?

1140
01:19:24,876 --> 01:19:27,410
Let's sit down.

1141
01:19:31,449 --> 01:19:32,950
[Man's Voice]
Hey, Rock.

1142
01:19:33,017 --> 01:19:34,952
[Sean's Voice]
They called my Dad Rock.

1143
01:19:36,221 --> 01:19:37,721
[Man's Voice]
Hey, Rock.

1144
01:19:39,357 --> 01:19:41,258
Hey Rock. Hey Rock.

1145
01:19:43,161 --> 01:19:44,561
Hey, Rock.

1146
01:19:45,563 --> 01:19:47,231
Hey, Rock.

1147
01:19:47,298 --> 01:19:48,765
- Get out of the--
- [Window Shattering]

1148
01:19:50,768 --> 01:19:52,336
[Screaming]

1149
01:19:52,403 --> 01:19:54,071
[Man's Voice]
Time's up, Rock.

1150
01:19:54,138 --> 01:19:57,741
- Bitch!
- Don't you ever touch me!

1151
01:19:57,808 --> 01:20:00,577
Calm down!
Calm down.

1152
01:20:00,644 --> 01:20:03,380
You like to hurt people?

1153
01:20:03,447 --> 01:20:05,782
What, you got
a death wish, jerk-off?

1154
01:20:05,850 --> 01:20:07,584
Sean.
You like hurting people, right?

1155
01:20:07,651 --> 01:20:10,720
- I'm gonna hurt you, you stupid prick.
- I don't think so.

1156
01:20:10,788 --> 01:20:12,589
[Chuckling]

1157
01:20:27,205 --> 01:20:29,973
[Glass Shattering]

1158
01:20:38,316 --> 01:20:39,616
[Girl Shrieks]

1159
01:20:53,464 --> 01:20:56,099
What are you, crazy?
What the hell just happened?

1160
01:20:56,167 --> 01:20:59,002
- Give me your keys.
- I can't give you my keys, man. I gotta get home.

1161
01:20:59,070 --> 01:21:00,570
Give me your fucking keys!

1162
01:21:31,669 --> 01:21:33,570
[Man's Voice]
Hey, Rock.

1163
01:21:33,637 --> 01:21:36,206
[Overlapping Voices]

1164
01:21:50,021 --> 01:21:51,521
[Shrieks]

1165
01:21:51,589 --> 01:21:52,722
Shut up!

1166
01:21:52,790 --> 01:21:55,158
Terry, stop screaming
and get us out of here.

1167
01:21:55,226 --> 01:21:57,527
Mom, are we lost?
Yes, honey. We're lost.

1168
01:21:57,595 --> 01:21:59,662
We're not lost.
[Bangs]

1169
01:21:59,730 --> 01:22:02,832
- [Terry] The guy just hit our car.
- [Mary] Wait, Terry.

1170
01:22:02,900 --> 01:22:04,534
Will you stop giving me shit?

1171
01:22:08,339 --> 01:22:09,839
What's going on, Mom?

1172
01:22:09,907 --> 01:22:13,076
Your dad's just getting information
so we can get the car fixed.

1173
01:22:13,144 --> 01:22:15,512
Time's up, Rock.

1174
01:22:15,579 --> 01:22:17,680
Fuck off, man.

1175
01:22:17,748 --> 01:22:19,149
Oh, my God.

1176
01:22:19,217 --> 01:22:20,917
Shit!

1177
01:22:23,587 --> 01:22:26,056
[Screaming]

1178
01:22:27,791 --> 01:22:30,160
Sean, get out of the car!

1179
01:22:30,228 --> 01:22:32,729
Get out of the--
Sean!

1180
01:22:32,796 --> 01:22:33,663
Mom!

1181
01:22:33,731 --> 01:22:35,432
[Gunshot]

1182
01:23:26,551 --> 01:23:28,118
[Clicking]

1183
01:23:53,811 --> 01:23:55,912
[Dialing]

1184
01:24:00,818 --> 01:24:03,019
Yeah, there's a break-in
at my house.

1185
01:24:04,622 --> 01:24:07,157
2014 Ryder Street.

1186
01:24:16,834 --> 01:24:18,168
Sean.

1187
01:24:24,842 --> 01:24:26,176
Sean.

1188
01:24:33,518 --> 01:24:35,818
Oh, my God.

1189
01:24:35,886 --> 01:24:37,820
Sean?

1190
01:24:37,888 --> 01:24:39,456
Hey, Dad.

1191
01:24:42,193 --> 01:24:44,161
Sean, what are you doing?

1192
01:24:44,895 --> 01:24:46,263
I--

1193
01:24:46,330 --> 01:24:48,365
Are you drunk?

1194
01:24:48,432 --> 01:24:50,433
Yep.

1195
01:24:50,501 --> 01:24:52,202
Just like you, Dad.

1196
01:24:53,604 --> 01:24:56,139
Remember when you were
drunk all the time?

1197
01:24:58,075 --> 01:25:00,544
Remember those days, Dad?

1198
01:25:02,380 --> 01:25:04,347
'Cause I do.

1199
01:25:04,415 --> 01:25:07,884
I remember this one time...

1200
01:25:07,951 --> 01:25:09,452
with the belt.

1201
01:25:09,520 --> 01:25:12,422
And you were going
in on me real good!

1202
01:25:12,490 --> 01:25:15,692
But Mom got in the way,
and you didn't like that, did you, Dad?

1203
01:25:17,861 --> 01:25:19,429
So it was Mom's turn.

1204
01:25:19,497 --> 01:25:21,364
But she was
a lot bigger than me.

1205
01:25:21,432 --> 01:25:24,867
So you could really put your shoulder into it.
Right, Dad!

1206
01:25:28,005 --> 01:25:29,405
I--

1207
01:25:29,473 --> 01:25:31,507
I remember...

1208
01:25:31,575 --> 01:25:34,043
standing there--

1209
01:25:34,111 --> 01:25:36,412
Watched you beat her!

1210
01:25:38,182 --> 01:25:40,016
And I--

1211
01:25:40,084 --> 01:25:43,486
And I just stood there,
and I did nothing!

1212
01:25:45,890 --> 01:25:51,560
Because I was afraid that you
would start hitting me again!

1213
01:26:00,537 --> 01:26:02,906
I was a coward then.

1214
01:26:07,144 --> 01:26:08,644
But I'm not
a coward anymore.

1215
01:26:08,712 --> 01:26:11,881
- Whoa! Whoa! Put the gun down!
- For fucking money?

1216
01:26:11,949 --> 01:26:14,717
- Get that gun outta my face.
- Piece of shit! For fucking money?

1217
01:26:14,785 --> 01:26:17,887
- What are you talking about?
- You know what I'm talking about!

1218
01:26:17,955 --> 01:26:20,356
Don't treat me like a kid.
I'm not stupid.

1219
01:26:20,424 --> 01:26:22,858
You understand?
I'm not fucking stupid.

1220
01:26:25,195 --> 01:26:27,663
I'm talking
about Larry Childs.

1221
01:26:29,766 --> 01:26:30,766
What?

1222
01:26:30,834 --> 01:26:32,802
Yeah, your old pal Larry.

1223
01:26:33,870 --> 01:26:35,638
How much money
did you get for her?

1224
01:26:35,705 --> 01:26:37,573
How much was she worth?

1225
01:26:37,641 --> 01:26:40,910
You motherfucker.
You don't know what the fuck you're talking about.

1226
01:26:40,978 --> 01:26:43,479
Now put the fucking gun-- I do
know what I'm talking about!

1227
01:26:43,547 --> 01:26:45,048
Yes, I do.

1228
01:26:45,115 --> 01:26:47,917
You collected money
on her life insurance.

1229
01:26:47,985 --> 01:26:49,953
What?

1230
01:26:50,020 --> 01:26:52,555
That's how we got out
of that shit neighborhood!

1231
01:26:52,622 --> 01:26:55,491
Yeah.
Sean, you better get that fucking gun out of my face.

1232
01:26:55,559 --> 01:26:57,726
- And I mean now.
- Stay the fuck back.

1233
01:26:57,794 --> 01:27:00,796
- Get that fucking gun out of my face.
- Stay the fuck back!

1234
01:27:00,864 --> 01:27:03,666
Goddamn it!
You think I killed my wife?

1235
01:27:03,733 --> 01:27:06,135
Your mother?
Is that what you think?

1236
01:27:06,203 --> 01:27:08,171
I know you did.
I know you did!

1237
01:27:08,238 --> 01:27:10,940
You don't know shit.

1238
01:27:14,878 --> 01:27:18,281
Larry Childs. Okay.

1239
01:27:19,749 --> 01:27:21,951
So, yeah,
I knew Larry Childs.

1240
01:27:22,752 --> 01:27:24,820
You must have seen him.

1241
01:27:24,888 --> 01:27:27,857
But you didn't recognize him
from that night, Sean.

1242
01:27:27,924 --> 01:27:30,259
I heard him call you Rock.

1243
01:27:30,327 --> 01:27:32,061
Your nickname Rock!

1244
01:27:32,129 --> 01:27:35,498
Sean! You're wrong. Okay?

1245
01:27:36,700 --> 01:27:39,702
You made a mistake then,
and you're making one now.

1246
01:27:42,239 --> 01:27:45,008
Now, what is more likely,

1247
01:27:45,075 --> 01:27:48,044
that I had your mother killed,
my wife,

1248
01:27:48,112 --> 01:27:51,780
for that life insurance money,

1249
01:27:51,848 --> 01:27:55,851
or that I didn't get you the help
you needed when you needed it?

1250
01:27:58,489 --> 01:28:00,756
What kind of man
do you think I am?

1251
01:28:12,002 --> 01:28:13,602
Okay.

1252
01:28:18,775 --> 01:28:21,444
I'm sorry. Sorry.

1253
01:28:21,512 --> 01:28:23,879
Don't be.
Don't be sorry.

1254
01:28:23,947 --> 01:28:26,382
It'll be okay.

1255
01:28:26,450 --> 01:28:29,185
I'm sorry
I can't believe you.

1256
01:28:31,288 --> 01:28:33,389
[Gunshot]

1257
01:28:52,876 --> 01:28:54,643
[Sean]
He killed her.

1258
01:28:55,579 --> 01:28:58,047
Hired that animal
to kill her.

1259
01:28:59,783 --> 01:29:02,318
Where's your father, Sean?

1260
01:29:02,386 --> 01:29:04,520
Somebody broke in.

1261
01:29:05,622 --> 01:29:08,424
I found him
in the basement.

1262
01:29:10,727 --> 01:29:12,228
He's dead.

1263
01:29:20,804 --> 01:29:24,039
You said you wanted
to help me, Teresa.

1264
01:29:38,688 --> 01:29:40,623
[Sean]
My name is Sean Donovan.

1265
01:29:40,690 --> 01:29:44,427
When I was nine years,
a woman was murdered in front of my eyes.

1266
01:29:46,463 --> 01:29:48,531
Her name was Mary Donovan.

1267
01:29:49,899 --> 01:29:52,034
She was my mother.

1268
01:29:59,643 --> 01:30:02,378
My life changed that night.

1269
01:30:02,446 --> 01:30:04,713
It changed
how I see the world.

1270
01:30:08,652 --> 01:30:12,555
I tell you this because I think that
night changed your life as well.

1271
01:30:14,258 --> 01:30:17,026
I know the suffering
you must go through every day,

1272
01:30:17,093 --> 01:30:19,629
hearing the cries of
your victims in your head,

1273
01:30:19,696 --> 01:30:22,331
seeing my mother's face
in your dreams,

1274
01:30:22,399 --> 01:30:25,901
praying that one day
the pain will stop.

1275
01:30:33,009 --> 01:30:35,744
That is why I write you today.

1276
01:30:35,812 --> 01:30:38,247
To help you ease your pain.

1277
01:30:39,550 --> 01:30:42,751
To let you know that I forgive you for what you did.

1278
01:30:48,192 --> 01:30:49,858
I ask only this,

1279
01:30:49,926 --> 01:30:52,261
that you help ease my pain.

1280
01:30:52,329 --> 01:30:55,698
Let me know if my father
was a part of this murder.

1281
01:30:55,765 --> 01:30:57,733
Let me clear my conscience...

1282
01:30:57,801 --> 01:31:00,269
and let my mother
rest in peace.

1283
01:31:10,280 --> 01:31:11,980
All I want is the truth.

1284
01:31:12,048 --> 01:31:15,551
The truth, and I will stay quiet
for the rest of my life.

1285
01:31:19,489 --> 01:31:22,024
I've provided you with
a safe way to answer me.

1286
01:31:22,092 --> 01:31:26,929
I've included a return envelope
and two stamps.

1287
01:31:26,996 --> 01:31:31,133
Place the black stamp on the
envelope if my father is guilty,

1288
01:31:31,201 --> 01:31:32,901
the red stamp if he's not.

1289
01:31:34,204 --> 01:31:35,471
Childs.

1290
01:31:43,213 --> 01:31:45,448
[Sean] I implore you to help me in this matter,

1291
01:31:45,515 --> 01:31:49,652
as it would be hard for me to
continue forgiving you if you do not.

1292
01:32:08,438 --> 01:32:10,606
I wish you well, Mr. Childs.

1293
01:32:15,512 --> 01:32:18,514
Sincerely,
Sean Donovan.

1294
01:32:33,664 --> 01:32:35,298
[Gasping]
